                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Yes, all categories of people are equal in the eyes of the law and have the same social standing."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "No, laws still exist that ban certain groups from resources and segregate society into racial and ethnic categories."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "Yes and no, all races and ethnicities are technically equal under the law, but they do not have equal social standing."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Yes and no, while people of all races and ethnicities have equal social standing, few people want to interact with others different from themselves."
